ember</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/9/02 1:13:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=58.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Lifter</span><hr size=1> Can anyone tell me how much each point adds to your total weight capacity? I've been thinking about it, cuz I heard someone put points in that (don't know how much) and he's now able to carry a whole ram on himself. I think a skald being able to carry a full ram might be interesting. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ufubbor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fubbor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Member</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/9/02 9:03:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=58.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lifter</span><hr size=1> well you get a free try this week , see my other post for info, so get level on lifter and then test it out then get level 2 then test it.  I agree if level on will let you carrie a ram solo that would be great for a skald for only one point <p>Icebane  50 Skald Lancelot,</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uvoleg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Voleg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Member</span><br>  Posts: 57<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/9/02 11:01:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=58.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lifter</span><hr size=1> its actually pretty nice.... somewhere around a 15% increase or so.... so the more str you have, the more bonus you get from lifter.  I will give you some exact numbers when i get home from work. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uanappo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>anappo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/10/02 7:07:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=58.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lifter</span><hr size=1> &gt; somewhere around a 15% increase or so.... <br><br>Nope. I have seen several reports of it being 20%<br><br>And that 20% is applied AFTER the buffs. With nice shaman buffs and 1 level in lifter, a skald should be capable of carrying a ram easily.<br><br>Let me elaborate.<br><br>Weight of a full ram is 236.<br><br>Ram Beak weights 52.<br>Ram Cladding weights 35.<br>Swing Harnesses weights 37, need 2, so the total weight is 74.<br>1 pack of 100 ironwood weights 25, 3 packs weight 75.<br><br>52 + 35 + 37 + 37 + 75 =  236<br><br>Add weight of yer regular equippment, say 44 to make a nice round figure. Total encumberance 280.<br><br>To get 280 with lvl 1 lifter, you would need str 234 (234 x 1.2 = 280.8)  <br><br>Good portion of that 234 can come from shaman buffs. You don't need all that highlevel shaman either.<br><br>Shaman aug baseline lvl 25 str buff yields +39 str<br>Shaman aug specline lvl 19 str/con buff yields +42 str<br><br>With both these buffs, one would need unbuffed str 153 to carry a full ram. Easily achieveable with all those +str items.<br><br>Never mind shamen. With a lifter, troll thanes can carry a ram with self buffs only.<br><br>To sum it up, lifter is truly a godsend. Logistictics of large scale siege operations was a nightmare (in 1.45 we are still playing on euro servers, ram needs 600 wood, not 300). This nightmare will be no more.<br><br>Ottar<br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uanappo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>anappo</A> at: 5/10/02 7:09:18 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ugrowlloud.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GrowlLoud</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/10/02 7:38:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=58.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lifter</span><hr size=1> My str is at 208, one point raised my max enc to aroun 240ish.  Not bad but not yet sure if its worth the precious points.<br><br>Growl Loud<br>GM of Fury (Kay)<br>50 Troll Skald <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/udarkith.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Darkith</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Member</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/10/02 9:14:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=58.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://asgarthvanguard.com/images/avcrest.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lifter</span><hr size=1> Lifter 1 added 33 points to my enc.<br><br>My Str is 214. <p>-----------------------------------<br><b>Darkith - lvl 50 Troll Skald</b><br><a href="http://asgarthvanguard.com"><b>[ Asgarth's Vanguard ]</b></a><br><b>Iseult</b></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign